Job Description
OT Services Delivery Manager (ROC)
To help better serve Fugro' s business needs we are looking for an OT Services Delivery Manager. You are a strong, process driven, leader who is responsible for being the single point of contact between Operational Technology Services, Fugros Business and Innovation teams as they support the development, deployment and support of Fugros Digital Workflow processes and related systems. They will manage relationships with Operational Technology Services various stakeholders to ensure success of Fugros drive towards digitization of Business processes.
You will be a champion of standardization of both designs and practices. Everything developed will meet the requirements of security, scalability, resiliency and ease of use.
Your role
You work closely with Digital Workflow Project development teams and innovation to set the general methodology and objectives for these services, thereby streamlining them with the company’s overall goals/objectives;
You interact with the Solution Owners & Product Owners for the various applications involved with the workflows to ensure streamlined support and to ensure that all aspects of each solution/product is understood;
You manage the Service Level agreements with Business entities and Solution/Product owners;
You also manage resources required to deliver and support the service and changes to the services using recognized procedures;
You assess, analyze and report reliability and performance of all aspects of the service.
Your track record
You have an Engineering, Information Technology or relevant professional experience and at least 7 years’ relevant working experience;
You have experience in IT environments including, but not limited to, software development, application lifecycle, networking, and IT security, cloud services, or project management. With a strong emphasis on support of data centers or remote operations;
You are fluent in English, both written and oral;
You have good stakeholder engagement skills and a healthy degree of business acumen and interest;
As a plus, you have experience working in a matrix organization and leading with influence rather than authority.
What Fugro offers
A competitive salary;
29 holidays per year based on a fulltime employment (of which 4 are appointed by Fugro management) and the possibility to purchase 12 additional days;
Extensive career & training opportunities both nationally and internationally;
Flexible working hours and the ability to work from home in accordance with your manager and corporate policies;
Commuting allowance;
Modern pension scheme;
Collective health insurance;
Possibility to register with our corporate fitness plan;
Coaching options through our EAP (Employee Assistance Program).
