The position
Are you an innovator in optimizing procurement processes with a clear focus on contract management? Are you a strong communicator and do you like to take control in order to increase the utilization of contracts? If yes, then we can offer you an exciting step in your career!

As a Contract Manager Temporary Labour you will serve as a “linking pin” between key stakeholders, the team of flex worker specialists (FlexOord), suppliers and the category manager temporary labour and will manage and optimize utilization of the contracts, including making recommendations, record keeping, monitoring, change management, and more to minimize the risk. You will be part of the NPR team of 8 colleagues within category management department of procurement and will support the category manager temporary labour with vendor selection and contracting by means of best value RFP process.
Your responsibilities
As a Contract Manager Temporary Labour you:

develop and implement procedures for contract management and administration in compliance with company policy, laws and regulations on a tactical level and strategic level;
are responsible for system registration of new/renewed supplier contracts (by category management), monitor utilization and recommend changes;
ensure that signed contracts are communicated to all relevant parties to provide contract visibility and awareness, interpretation to support implementation;
develop a performance measurement plan, prepares and executes evaluation reports in cooperation with key stakeholders and supplier;
serve as the point of contact for internal customers like the FlexOord team on contractual matters. Act as contractual “middleman” ensuring timely review and approval / reconciliation of variations;
develop and maintain an open and positive relationship with key stakeholder and supplier;
ensure contract close-out, extension or renewal.
Job requirements
You have a BSc degree, preferably in business administration;
3 to 5 years relevant working experience in contract management;
A good knowledge of different types of contracts and experience in procurement of temporary labour;
Relevant experience in implementation of change and strong analytical skills;
You take ownership and are strong in persuasion and motivation;
Excellent communication skills and organizational sensitivity;
Good common in English and Dutch speaking and writing;
Take the lead and feel comfortable in commercial negotiations.
We offer
Working in an international, high demanding and dynamic organisation, with the possibility to truly have impact on our business, people and environment. We offer a complete package with excellent secondary employment benefits. The package includes among other things:

a salary that matches your responsibilities and experience;

Travel allowance (€0.31 per km) and home office allowance (€2,15 per day);

32 leave days per year;

Variable bonus;

Pension scheme;

Collective health insurance (optional);

Flexible working from home policy, 2 days a week when working on a full-time basis;

Extensive learning and (personal) development possibilities, including a wide range of online courses via Goodhabitz;

You can join communities, like Young Van Oord, Van Oord Women and the Van Oord staff association;

We organise several (sport) events, e.g. winter sport, weekend of sailing, cycling and a motorcycle tour.

