Within our Finance & Control department, the Global Financial Shared Service Center (GFSSC) is on an exciting journey to positioning itself as the “go to” department for centrally executed financial services. This journey includes defining and launching new services, introducing new technologies and onboarding new internal clients.
The central Finance & Control (F&C) Department within Van Oord consists of four sub-departments:
Group Reporting & Control;
Global Financial Shared Service Centre (GFSSC);
Group Fiscal Affairs;.
International Project Controllers Pool
The F&C department consists of 125 FTE and is responsible for financial and business control on group level, for tax advice, consolidation and reporting and operates a pool of project controllers. The GFSSC provides central accounting and payroll services for business units and projects and consists of 67 FTE spread across our Rotterdam and Dubai hubs.
Your responsibilities
As a GFSSC Cost Controller you will support Van Oord staff departments like HR, QHSE, Survey, etc. You will be the one who provides real time insights in actual costs versus budget for the Staff Directors. You are the trusted financial advisor for our clients. You spot improvements and initiate opportunities to increase the effectiveness and efficiency of our financial processes.
To be successful in your job you:
Provide periodic reports and analysis of General Overhead costs, actuals as well as forecasts;
Liaise with Staff Directors who are your client;
Control the budget of internal department projects;
Contribute to the Planning & Control cycle with respect to the (Annual) Plan process;
Support in (external) audits and follow up of the management letter;
Work on improving the insights of the General Overhead for Staff Directors;
Analyse the General Overhead costs (in the workflow) and adjust when needed;
Improve the quality of the General Overhead figures to minimizing the number of corrections;
Contribute to our ambition on further developing Business Intelligence and Data Management capabilities;
Co-develop dashboards for General Overhead monitoring, deliver real time information of actuals / budgets to the Staff Directors / Staf Controller (in cooperation with our Change team and using the process mining tool Celonis);
Develop General Overhead reporting for the Staff Directors / Staff Controller so the quarterly report can be delivered earlier and with better quality;
Job requirements
We are looking for people with strong initiative and the ability to act as a self-starter, being able to identify opportunities to drive value. You are agile, resilient, and flexible with the ability to react quickly to a changing environment. Attention to detail and a drive to follow and complete processes are very important. You have a natural drive and commitment to liaise with business stakeholders as their trusted partner. Further, you have the following competencies:
Effective team player with strong communicative skills;
Accurate, analytical and decisive;
Culturally and organizational sensitive;
High level of service drive and commitment to business stakeholders;
Ability to communicate effectively with employees from all over the world;
Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration with a minimum 2-4 years of relevant experience in an international business environment;
Fluent in English, verbal as well as written;
Digital savviness;
A continuous improvement mindset (preferably Lean Green belt);
Relevant experience in a project environment is a preference.
